The study by scientists of the National Trust for Scotland will analyze common dwarf bats and pygmy bats, as well as ear bats and water bats from the Inverewe Gardens of Western Ross.
Special recording equipment will be located in key places around the property to track the activity of bats during the season.
The NHS team and volunteers will also carry out mobile studies using manual detectors.
The specialized audio analysis of all recordings will estimate the frequency of sounds made by bats and what species emit certain sounds.
There will be products and a map of the habitat and a report, to create a detailed, scaled picture of their behavior in the environment.
