"Here at Thrave, the area is wonderful for bats," he says.
"We have old buildings, a lot of old trees and a perfect habitat.
But there are many things we don't know about bats, so the work we do here and elsewhere will help us understand why they need them to multiply."
It stresses the importance of searching bats before performing maintenance work on property, because simply unintentional destruction of a maternal nest could kill up to 400 females and chickens, which can destroy the entire local population.
The bats are protected, and killing, harassing or disturbing them, as well as destroying their nests, are forbidden actions.
