Both counts may receive a capital sentence, according to the court's document.
A few weeks after the attack, a large federal jury accused Saipov of 22 counts of charges including eight criminal charges in support of organised crime, usually used by federal prosecutors in organised crime cases, as well as an accusation of violence and destruction of motorized vehicles.
